.TH "uclogic_params_get_str_desc" 9 "uclogic_params_get_str_desc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
uclogic_params_get_str_desc \- retrieve a string descriptor from a HID device interface, putting it into a kmalloc-allocated buffer as is, without character encoding conversion.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" uclogic_params_get_str_desc
.BI "(__u8 **pbuf "  ","
.BI "struct hid_device *hdev "  ","
.BI "__u8 idx "  ","
.BI "size_t len "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pbuf" 12
Location for the kmalloc-allocated buffer pointer containing
the retrieved descriptor. Not modified in case of error.
Can be NULL to have retrieved descriptor discarded.
.IP "hdev" 12
The HID device of the tablet interface to retrieve the string
descriptor from. Cannot be NULL.
.IP "idx" 12
Index of the string descriptor to request from the device.
.IP "len" 12
Length of the buffer to allocate and the data to retrieve.
.SH "RETURN"
number of bytes retrieved (<= len),
-EPIPE, if the descriptor was not found, or
another negative errno code in case of other error.
